<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
</head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Functions</title>
</head>
<body>
<!-- pipelining, output from the previous is input for the next -->
    {{index . 0}}
    {{index . 1}}
    {{index . 2}}
    <!--
    index
    a func you can use in a template
    it is a "prefefined gloabal function"

    Index returns  the result of indexing its first argument by the
     following arguments. Thus "index x 1 2 3" is, in Go syntax,
     x[1][2][3]. Each indexeed item must be a map, slice, or array.

     https://godoc.org/text/template#hdr-Functions
    -->

    <!-- FYI -->
    This ia a go template comment
    {{/*(index .Achivement 3).Name*/}}
</body>
</html>